<TEXT>
john ulric nef a retired university of chicago 
economics professor died sunday at his home here he was 89 
nef who had been suffering from parkinsons disease died of a 
stroke 
the chicago native taught economic history at the university of 
chicago from 1929 until retiring in 1964 and he helped found the 
committee on social thought at the university 
nef was an army veteran of world war i who was graduated from 
harvard university and received a doctorate in economic history from 
what is now the brookings institution 
he moved to washington in the 1960s and became a members of the 
cosmos club an exclusive organization whose members include 
toplevel government officials 
nef wrote 12 books including the rise of the british coal 
industry and he had been a visiting professor in france 
survivors include his wife evelyn of washington whom he married 
in 1964 
</TEXT>
