have contributed to the lesser turnout a judge ruled last week 
against retailers who sought permission to open all day monday 
although filenes and other stores around bostons downtown 
crossing appeared quieter than normal other shopping malls in the 
region reported good turnouts 
the stores picked up around noon said beth chase a clerk at 
bloomingdales at the chestnut hill mall i think a lot of people 
got up late had brunch and then went shopping 
but some store managers already had their minds on other holiday 
happiness to sell 
valentines day goes up tomorrow said joann demilner 
manager of galas hallmark in suburban detroit 
