earlier this year wyoming indignantly 
became the last state in the nation to raise its legal drinking age 
to 21 next month the legislature will be asked to display its rage 
by lowering it back to 19 
the request comes barely six months after the higher age limit 
took effect and is seen by its sponsors as a way to defend the us 
constitution and to rise up against federal blackmail 
it also comes in the wake of a study showing that the 
singlevehicle nighttime crash fatality rate among drivers ages 19 
and 20 declined 38 percent in tennessee in the 28 months after that 
state raised its drinking age from 19 to 21 
wyoming raised its drinking age when faced with a federal mandate 
that threatened loss of millions of dollars in highway funds 
