<TEXT>
the chinese people must be prepared for two or 
three hard years while the government imposes austerity measures to 
battle economic problems the communist partys official daily 
newspaper said monday 
the masses must tighten their belts for the next few years as the 
nation comes to grips with faltering agricultural production high 
inflation and overspending of public funds the peoples daily said 
in a frontpage commentary 
the editorial was the latest piece in the official media to 
hammer home the seriousness of the economic crisis which has seen 
inflation soar to 26 percent and industrial growth shoot up to an 
unsustainable level of almost 20 percent 
although incomes as a whole are rising surveys have shown that 
up to 20 percent of urban residents report that their living 
standards are declining as a result of the rise in retail prices 
in september the government announced a twoyear economic 
retrenchment plan under which the government will slash funding for 
new construction projects impose controls over credit prices and 
raw materials distribution and slow the pace of marketoriented 
reforms 
the measures have had some small successes in cooling off the 
economy but have run into resistance from local authorities trying 
to protect pet projects 
the overheated economy can be cooled down and economic health 
restored only when all departments consider the interests of the 
whole and share the burden the daily said 
it said that although the economy looks very good as a result of 
rapid economic expansion there are in fact a lot of potential 
dangers 
the foundation of the economy is weak it said with a large 
population inadequate natural resources and a shortage of funds 
but many people have forgotten this 
new buildings continue to go up while some localities compete for 
high economic growth and indiscriminately distribute big bonuses 
among employees 
some people import goods blindly and spend foreign currency 
without plan and some people eat and drink and spend money 
extravagantly if we dont cool down the overheated economy it 
will surely lead to crisis 
the daily said the need to live a hard life does not mean that 
economic construction will be halted rather there will be a shift 
from dependence on increasing investment and expanding production to 
reliance on improving management upgrading technology and raising 
economic efficiency 
