north korea on monday invited radical 
students from south korea to an international youth festival next 
year in its capital according to a north korean letter 
officials said the letter was sent through the border village of 
panmunjom and addressed to south koreas national council of student 
representatives a radical student organization 
the letter called for the two sides to meet at the border in 
march to arrange the participation of south korean students in the 
13th world festival of youth and students to be held july 18 in 
the north korean capital of pyongyang 
in the invitation north korea characterized the international 
festival as an event where students seeking the unification of the 
divided peninsula can form a common movement 
the peninsula was divided in 1945 at then end of world war ii 
when soviet and us troops ended japans colonial rule 
the quadrennial festival is a political arts and sports event in 
which most of the participants are from communist and third world 
nations the last such festival was held in moscow in 1985 
radical students said there was no reason to avoid our 
participation in events in north korea but government officials 
maintain that all dialogue with north korea should be conducted 
through government channels 
south korean officials said the radical students were invited to 
strengthen antius and antigovernment activism 
in june and august police blocked thousands of radical students 
who tried to stage a crosscountry march to the border where they 
were to hold unification talks with north korean students the 
police blockades triggered violent street protests 
radical students a small but powerful minority on campuses have 
seized on national unification as part of their antigovernment 
antius strategy but they have failed to garner strong public 
support 
north korea in recent months has called for dialogue with seoul 
through various channels but south korean officials consider the 
overtures as attempts to remove us troops and cause social unrest 
dissident students are demanding the withdrawal of 42000 us 
troops based in south korea under a mutual defense treaty saying 
the united states has hampered unification 
in preparation for the youth festival north korea is building 
new hotels in pyongyang with a capacity of 2600 guests the 
official north korean news agency reported monday the korean 
central news agency said one facility the 33story chongnyon hotel 
will have a glass roof indoor and an outdoor swimming pools a 
