california roll cbs osamu 
 
east is east and west is west right 
not according to japanese composer and musician osamu whos 
successfully blended traditional oriental rhythms with fasterpaced 
jazz and rock on california roll 
for western music lovers whove heard some pleasing eastern tunes 
but dont know what to buy at the record store california roll 
is an ideal aurally palatable introduction 
the album which is osamu kitajimas third in the united states 
is a showcase for the chinese koto a 13string zitherlike 
instrument that emits the precise delicate sound familiar to 
westerners as oriental music 
but dont get the idea that california roll is nothing but 
inscrutable meandering its too full of stateoftheart 
electronics for that 
osamu plays all the instruments on four of the nine songs that 
feature the koto surrounded by a patter of percussion bells and 
synthesized sounds 
songs such as escape space back street to paradise and 
white in flight with their sensitive melodies and 
slowerthanslow rhythms lend a sensation of limbolike suspension 
to the listener they also wouldnt sound out of place on a miami 
vice soundtrack 
osamu can rip out a hot rock guitar lick as well on leading 
edge the guitar stakes out the melody followed by a bridge on 
the koto eastern eyes western skies features an extended 
guitar solo as does the even harderrocking samurai lover 
the title of california roll refers to an american version of 
that japanese favorite sushi osamus musical synthesis gives 
western ears a taste of that countrys sonic delicacy 
by curt anderson associated press writer 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
big time island tom waits 
 
much of tom waits music is difficult but big time is 
impossible the poor sound quality makes it that way 
big time released in conjunction with the concert film of 
the same name contains live performances of songs from waits three 
most recent studio albums swordfishtrombone rain dogs and 
franks wild years fans already familiar with the material may 
find big time of interest but the uninitiated likely will be 
frustrated by the task of trying to decipher waits lyrics 
when his gravelcoated voice isnt too far from the mike its 
too close and on three songs that were mixed live to cassette the 
singing is overwhelmed by tape hiss its too bad because the 
enigmatic waits is clever with words a lyric sheet would have 
helped but waits fivepiece backup band is mired in aural muck 
too 
there are times when sound quality that is less than 
stateoftheart enhances a performance bruce springsteens 
nebraska album comes to mind and waits last of the beatniks 
is anything but a digital performer but the smalltime sound on 
big time causes the medium to block the message 
by steven wine associated press writer 
