mike warnke is one of a kind hes part 
evangelist and part standup comic or as some folks say hes a 
standup jimmy swaggart with long hair 
the 43yearold christian humorist and recording artist who has 
shoulderlength locks is also a former heroin addict and satanist 
high priest who once had more than 1500 worshippers 
noting his background he says if god can use me he can use 
anybody 
he shares his religious faith at up to 22 personal appearances a 
month hes just released his 12th humor album one in a 
million on dayspring records of nashville 
he employs 30 people at his ministry office in burgin ky where 
he has noted a marked rise in telephone calls from people including 
the police asking about the occult 
theres been a dramatic increase in the past three years he 
said in a telephone interview were seeing younger kids getting 
involved it used to be people age 20 but now its 13 and 14 id 
say 70 percent of the calls deal with the occult this is a 
frightening trend 
warnke who wrote the 1972 book the satan seller which has 
sold more than 3 million copies believes theres a definite link 
